The Springboks are set to begin a new era and will announce Rassie Erasmus' successor as coach. JOHANNESBURG - The Springboks are set to begin a new era and will announce Rassie Erasmus' successor as coach. Erasmus took over following Allister Coetzee's sacking in February 2018. WATCH: Boks victory not a panacea for unity He led South Africa to their third World Cup crown but announced that he would be returning to his previous post as director of rugby at SA Rugby. Jacques Nienaber is widely expected to get the nod. South Africa are set to name a new coach. Courtesy #DStv403